	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">S.</s>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">De <persName ref="p3242" cert="high">Utingero</persName> minim, quam scripseris lugubria<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1"><persName ref="p495" type="citizen_name" cert="high">Bullinger</persName> muß in einem nicht erhaltenen Brief über die Erkrankung <persName ref="p3242" cert="high">Heinrich Utingers</persName> berichtet haben (vgl. auch unten <ref target="file10933">Nr. 891</ref>, 11-16).</note>.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Deus adsit, precor, suo, sive vivat sive moriatur.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">De cęsare<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2">Offenbar hatte sich <persName ref="p495" type="citizen_name" cert="high">Bullinger</persName> nach Neuigkeiten über den Krieg zwischen Kaiser <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p18538" cert="high">Karl V.</persName> und König <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p20225" cert="high">Franz I.</persName> erkundigt.</note> nihil audio, nisi quod periculum instet <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l862" cert="high">Helvetiis</placeName>, si victor evasent.</s>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Hic rumor ex omnibus partibus advolat.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">In <placeName cert="high" type="citizen_name" ref="l2529">Brabantia</placeName> dicunt: Victor caesar invasurus est civitates foederatas (die handstett<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">Hauptstädte(?) wie <placeName ref="l518" cert="high">Utrecht</placeName>, <placeName ref="l1422" cert="high">Deventer</placeName> und <placeName ref="l1606" cert="high">Kampen</placeName>; vgl. <bibl>DRW</bibl> V 133.</note>) in <placeName ref="l20" cert="high">Germania Inferiore</placeName>.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Ex <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l832" cert="high">Gallus</placeName> scripsit his diebus ad me quidam<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Unbekannt; der Brief scheint nicht erhalten zu sein.</note> de incolumitate sua; de hoste ne verbum quidem.</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Mittunt vim auri ingentem huc milites <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l832" cert="high">Gallicani</placeName>.</s>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Misit et psitacum quidam.</s>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Ex quo securi mihi videntur plus satis.</s>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Ex <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l760" cert="high">Salodoro</placeName> locisque aliis nobis finitimis excurrendi<note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5">Gemeint ist: in den Dienst des <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l832" cert="high">französischen</placeName> Königs.</note> nullus est finis.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><pb type="edition" next="419"/>Caeterum de conventu, priusquam ego consulem adivi, deliberatum erat<note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6"><persName ref="p495" type="citizen_name" cert="high">Bullinger</persName> hatte <persName ref="p8418" cert="high">Myconius</persName> gebeten, dem Burgermeister <persName ref="p8129" cert="high">Jakob Meyer</persName> nahezulegen, eine eventuelle Tagung über die Konkordienfrage noch aufzuschieben; s. <persName ref="p8049" cert="high">Vadian</persName> BW V 362f (vgl. oben <ref target="file10925">Nr. 884</ref>, 5-8, und 885, 35-37).</note>.</s>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la" type="manual">Indictum aiebat consul in dominicam proximam ante Michaelis<note xml:id="fn7" type="footnote" n="7">24. September (s. <bibl>EA</bibl> IV/1c 745 10).</note>.</s>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Quid, si consilio tuorum differri posset?</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="15" xml:lang="la" type="auto">In <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l830" cert="high">Anglia</placeName> pax est.</s>
					<s n="16" xml:lang="la" type="auto">De regina necata<note xml:id="fn8" type="footnote" n="8">Zur Hinrichtung <persName ref="p4358" cert="high">Anne Boleyns</persName> am 18. Mai 1536 s. Geoffrey Rudolph <hi>Elton,</hi> Reform and Reformation. England 1509-1558, London 1977. - The New History of England, Bd. 2, S. 250-256.</note> et ipsi <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l830" cert="high">Angli</placeName> et finitimi dicunt:</s>
					<s n="17" xml:lang="de" type="manual">"Es ist ein böß stuck fleisch gsin<note xml:id="fn9" type="footnote" ana="lex" n="9">gewesen.</note>."</s>
					<s n="18" xml:lang="la" type="manual">Commune hoc.</s>
					<s n="19" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Suspecti possent igitur esse, quicunque de <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p8375" cert="high">rege</persName><note xml:id="fn10" type="footnote" n="10"><persName ref="p8375" cert="high">Heinrich VIII.</persName></note> male loquuntur.</s>
					<s n="20" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Ex compatre meo quodam<note xml:id="fn11" type="footnote" n="11">Unbekannt.</note> hęc dico, qui nudiustertius venit ex <placeName cert="high" type="citizen_name" ref="l2529">Brabantia</placeName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="21" xml:lang="la" type="auto" ana="farewell">Vale cum uxore<note xml:id="fn12" type="footnote" ana="bio" n="12"><persName ref="p8051" cert="high">Anna, geb. Adlischwyler</persName>.</note>, liberis<note xml:id="fn13" type="footnote" n="13">Siehe oben <ref target="file10782">Nr. 744</ref>, Anm. 34.</note> et fratribus.</s>
					<s n="22" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><persName ref="p3242" cert="high">Utingerum</persName>, si vivit, consolare in domino vel meo nomine.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="23" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><placeName ref="l28" cert="high">Basileae</placeName>, raptim, 6. septembris anno 1536.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="24" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tuus <persName ref="p8418" cert="high">Myconius</persName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="25" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Domino <persName ref="p495" type="citizen_name" cert="high">Heinricho Bullingero</persName>, domino et fratri suo charissimo.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
